snippet: Liberal Egyptians have long had an uneasy relationship with the military, but since the military pushed out President Mohamed Morsi, a majority of liberals have been intolerant of dissenters.
abstract: Hypernationalist euphoria unleashed in Egypt by the toppling of Pres Mohamed Morsi has swept up even liberals and leftists; liberal Egyptians have long had an uneasy relationship with the military, but since it pushed out Morsi, vast majority of liberals have joined in jubilation at defeat of Muslim Brotherhood, laying into any dissenters.

byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh and Asmaa Al Zohairy contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Liberal Egyptians have long had an uneasy relationship with the military, but since the military pushed out President Mohamed Morsi, a majority of liberals have been intolerant of dissenters.

headline.main: Egyptian Liberals Embrace the Military, Brooking No Dissent
headline.print_headline: Egyptian Liberals Embracing Army In Turnaround
